Sentencas: The first one is a conventional anode supported cell (ASC); and the other, namely CASC, contains an extra layer of Ni-Cu/Ni-Fe alloys-BaZroiCe(0.7)Y(0.1)Yb(0.1)O(3-delta), (NCF-BZCYYb) cermet catalyst on the surface of the anode-support.
